  "title": "Quantity Surveyor (Civil/Construction)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Visit www.ppsjob.com.sg</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Job Responsibilities</p>\n<p>Handle quotation, cost estimation and pricing with contractors</p>\n<p>Prepare &amp; award subcontracts for projects</p>\n<p>Manage all project cost control from initial calculations to final figures</p>\n<p>Evaluating Contractor’s proposal and specifications</p>\n<p>Prepare tender submission, handle progress claims &amp; progress payments, VO &amp; finalization of accounts</p>\n<p>Coordination on all documentations required by regulations with subcontractors to ensure smooth progress of works</p>\n<p>Review CS, architectural and M&amp;E drawings to ensure special requirements and annotations are taken into consideration and complete in the tenders</p>\n<p>Consult and align Construction team on the scope of tender submission; highlight and seek agreement on special requirements or unusual scope</p>\n<p>Monitor deduction for materials bought on behalf of subcontractors/suppliers</p>\n<p>Job Requirements</p>\n<p>1-5 years working experiences in general building construction industry</p>\n<p>min Diploma / Degree in Quantity Surveying &amp; relevant qualifications</p>\n<p>Proficiency in Microsoft Excel, Word, Power Point &amp; AutoCAD drafting</p>\n<p>Able to communicate fluently in English &amp; Mandarin (in order to liaise with the English &amp; Mandarin speaking associates)</p>\n<p>Good interpersonal and communication skills to work as a team</p>\n<p>Ability to communicate with people at all level and be meticulous with an eye for details</p>\n<p>5.5 days (9am - 6pm) (Alternate Saturdays)</p>",
